tyle=3D"margin:10px 0">Blue states impose top marginal income tax rates of =
10.9=E2=80=9313.3% (CA, NY, NJ) plus heavy regulations and high cost of liv=
ing. </p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Red states (TX, FL, TN, NV) have 0% sta=
te income tax and lower regulatory burdens. </p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">=
High earners and businesses are flocking disproportionately to Red States. =
I think it all began during Covid but now as deficits rise things are getti=
ng more desperate.  This is going to leave awful deficits for these blue st=
ates. </p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">The Logical Solution is to cut regs an=
d taxes and attract people or at least stem the bleed.  Instead of lowering=
 taxes/regs to compete, the blue states are jacking taxes and regulations o=
n remaining residents and businesses only to accelerate the outflow.</p><p =
style=3D"margin:10px 0">The result is a vicious cycle for blue states.  Tax=
 base GONE.... Industry GONE.... this is what happens when states elect mor=
ons without any fiscal understanding.  No offense to anyone here but it is =
sad for me to see this to happen to California (also IL and NY where i live=
d in a past life). </p><p></p></div></td></tr>
